#!/usr/bin/env bash
# SessionStart hook: inject the SDLC lifecycle gate in project repos.
# Emits nothing outside git repos (global-config sessions, scratch dirs).
[ "${AI_SDLC_SCRATCH:-}" = "1" ] && exit 0
git rev-parse --is-inside-work-tree >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 0
cat <<'EOF'
SDLC LIFECYCLE (from Pedro's global config):
1. Invoke Skill(sdlc-start) before the first substantive task of the session, and again to plan any multi-step or risky change. Small, reversible, obvious edits may go straight to the change.
2. Execution is governed by the engineering standard (sdlc-core/references/STANDARD.md): root cause over patch, smallest coherent change, verification ladder.
3. Invoke Skill(sdlc-finish) before declaring a nontrivial change done and before the session ends if anything changed — it is what makes the project resumable by the next session.
Scale ceremony with blast radius, not file count — config that propagates to other agents/machines is high blast radius even when the diff is small.
EOF
